{
    "$schema": "./nodes.schema.json",
    "_comment": [
        "The UNIVERSAL node describes nodes to include on every screen.",
        "Negative integers for a destination are relative indicators as to how many history steps to go back.",
        "Negative coordinates describe a number of cells from the last row or column.",
        "The `.` directory refers to the `assets/images` directory relative to the project root.",
        "Row -1 (bottom row) is reserved for UNIVERSAL nodes.",
        "Grid is 10x6 for standard usability. Hence grid coordinate indices are in [-10..-1] U [0..9] for x and [-6..-1] U [0..5] for y."
    ],
    "nodes": {
